# Model Routing

Match the model to the **responsibility level**, not the topic. Three tiers.

## Tiers

| Tier | Use for | Agent frontmatter `model:` | Task subagent slug / Cloud API slug |
|------|---------|----------------------------|-------------------------------------|
| **Vision** (high-stakes) | Big plans, product/business strategy, architecture decisions, high-risk reviews, delegation/orchestration, anything irreversible or expensive to get wrong | `claude-opus-4-8` | `claude-opus-4-8-thinking-high` |
| **Manager** (PM) | Planning, scoping, ticket/spec breakdown, splitting scope into executor-sized bricks, routine review | `claude-4.6-sonnet` (escalate to `claude-opus-4-8` for big plans) | `claude-4.6-sonnet-high-thinking` |
| **Executor** | The smallest concrete unit of work: one Task / one commit / one brick, mechanical edits, scaffolding from an approved spec | `composer-2.5-fast` | `composer-2.5-fast` |

> **Note:** "Agent frontmatter `model:`" names are the short identifiers used in `.cursor/agents/*.md` for the Cursor IDE. "Task subagent slug / Cloud API slug" are the full slugs required when spawning agents programmatically (Task tool or Cursor Cloud Agent API from CI scripts). Always use the full slug in `cursor-models.config.ts`.

## Routing rules

1. **Default down, escalate up.** Start at the lowest tier that can safely do the work. Escalate only when stakes, ambiguity, or blast radius demand it.
2. **Vision owns decisions, not typing.** A Vision-tier agent plans and reviews; it delegates execution to Executor-tier subagents.
3. **Manager splits, Executor builds.** A Manager turns a plan/spec into bricks sized for one commit; each brick goes to an Executor.
4. **High-risk review is Vision.** Security review, architecture review, business/legal-impacting review → `claude-opus-4-8`.
5. **One brick = one Executor.** Never hand an Executor a multi-surface plan; split first (Manager).
6. **Match the workflow stage** (default tier):

| Stage | Tier |
|-------|------|
| `/prd` (discover/converge/challenge), `/intake` triage+delegation, `/feature-area` map/validate | Vision |
| `/feature-area slice`, `/user-story`, `/spec`, `/task` propose/scaffold, planning | Manager |
| `/implement run`, `/task` implementation, code edits, scaffolding | Executor |
| Security / architecture / business review | Vision |

## When unsure

If you cannot tell whether a task is Manager or Executor, it is Manager (plan it first). If you cannot tell whether it is Vision or Manager, and it is irreversible or strategic, it is Vision.
